{
  "stem": "1917.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 15.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I was very disappointed in my mother.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I expected, as I think most children expect, for their mother to protect them.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I expected my mother to march to school and talk to the teacher.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But she didn't.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[SOB]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was-- somehow, I had to get over it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't think that I have ever accepted the fact-- not only that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They kept calling us dirty Jews.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I knew that I was cleaner than most of the other kids.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The books in school were filled with hatred against Jews.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "One of the math problems that I clearly remember, it said, when you have five Jews, and you kill three, how many are left?",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the reason that it's important to illustrate-- for people to understand that everything surrounding the hatred and destruction of the Jews was part of everyday life.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It wasn't just one little place.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was no place for us to go.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, I think that living in this-- we still went to school.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We tried to stay out of trouble.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we got spit on.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We got pushed around.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And of course, we couldn't go home to mother and complain, or to father, because that didn't help, either.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] By 1943, things got pretty tough.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Our house was often surrounded by Nazi young hoodlums who were harassing us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So we attended school-- not always-- could-- could not always could even leave the house.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We had to wear a yellow Star of David.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And things got even more intense at home and in school when we did go.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I cannot-- I think that most people cannot understand a school that would teach, endorse, and support hatred against one group or another.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Unfortunately, not fast enough.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
